               <msContents>
                  <summary>Inscribed dedication to Zeus.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">12 lines of text; lines 6 and 7 exhibit clear erasure.</note>
                     <note type="general">Dedication to Zeus by Philotera, daughter of Patentais.</note>
                     <note type="general">This inscription appears to be the final version of the text, while O.Ber. II 119 (found in the same trench as 118) appears to be the model or rough copy of the inscription.</note>
                     <note type="general">Lines 6 and 7 are erased due to the damnatio memoriae Nero suffered after his death.  For other evidence of Nero's damnatio in Egypt see O.Ber. II, p. 21.</note>
                     <note type="general">This block and its companion were reused in a wall of a substantial structure from the late fourth to fifth cent. A.D.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
